Former Managing Director of the Niger Delta Development Commission, NDDC, and a prominent member of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Timi Alaibe, has defected to the People’s Democratic Party, PDP, in Bayelsa State.
Other party’s bigwigs who left alongside Alaibe include former federal lawmakers, Michael Epengule and Nelson Belief, B.Z. Onniye, Ebamua Empere of the state legislature; former Secretary to Bayelsa State Government, Gideon Ekeuwei; one-time Commissioner for Youths and Sports, Kemi Prefa; ex-Chairman of Sagbama Local Government Area, Barnabas Edure and former Executive Secretary, SUBEB, Rhodesia Whyte.
Receiving Alaibe, Bayelsa State Governor, Seriake Dickson noted that the defection of the former NDDC MD and his followers did not only give credence to the supremacy of PDP but also signified the end of APC in the state. 